  "doc_id": "38396",
  "text": "RAG2 is highly unstable in the S, G2, and M phases of the cell cycle [CITATION_1] , and hence developing lymphocytes have periods during which RAG1 is present in the absence of RAG2. We propose that as RAG2 levels rise at the beginning of G1, RAG1 is already localized to recombination centers and facilitates the recruitment of RAG2 (pathway 2 above).",
  "correct_citation": {
